        "## Phase 2 - No-Show Prediction Model\n",
        "\n",
        "We fit a gradient-boosted classifier on the Kaggle data. Two methodological points worth flagging:\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Patient-level train/test split** via `GroupShuffleSplit` keyed on `PatientId` — so no patient appears in both train and test. This avoids identity leakage from the `prior_noshow_rate` feature, which would otherwise inflate AUC.\n",
        "- **Compared against logistic regression baseline** to confirm the GBM's advantage isn't dependent on opaque nonlinearities.\n",
        "\n",
        "The trained model is saved as a joblib artifact and used downstream by the simulator.\n"
      ]
    },
