        "## Phase 3 - Service-Time Distributions\n",
        "\n",
        "Physician consultation times are right-skewed - short modal visits with a long tail. We fit a **lognormal** distribution per NAMCS specialty category (1 = primary care, 2 = surgical, 3 = medical specialty). Check-in (approx. 3 min) and nurse intake (~10 min) are not measured by NAMCS, so we calibrate them to ratios from the operations-research literature (Cayirli & Veral 2003; Gupta & Denton 2008).\n"
      ]
