        "## Phase 5 - Multi-Stage Discrete-Event Simulator\n",
        "\n",
        "The simulator (built on SimPy) models one clinic-day:\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Patient arrival** at scheduled time (with small jitter), then queue through:\n",
        "- **Check-in** (capacity 2 desks, lognormal service ~3 min)\n",
        "- **Nurse intake** (capacity 6 nurses, lognormal service ~10 min)\n",
        "- **Physician consultation** (capacity 1 per provider, lognormal service per specialty)\n",
        "\n",
        "For each appointment, the no-show probability comes from the Phase 2 model, **rescaled** so the population mean equals a U.S. base rate of 18% (the model's Brazilian absolute level is anchored to U.S. literature).\n",
        "\n",
        "We also run a **sanity check** with no no-shows + no arrival jitter under both 6 nurses and 12 nurses — the wait should drop sharply when nurse capacity doubles, confirming both simulator correctness and that the nurse stage is the binding constraint.\n"
      ]
    },
