# Analysis pipeline

Team A11 — A Data-Driven Operations Framework for Patient Flow Management.

Six phases, each a runnable `.py`. End-to-end reproducible from `/datasets/` (see `../datasets/README.md`).

## Setup

From the project root:

```bash
python3 -m venv .venv
.venv/bin/pip install pandas numpy scipy scikit-learn simpy matplotlib seaborn pyreadstat pyarrow joblib
```

## Run everything

```bash
.venv/bin/python analysis/main.py
```

Or one phase at a time (each depends on the previous phase's output):

```bash
.venv/bin/python analysis/phase1_data_prep.py
.venv/bin/python analysis/phase2_noshow_model.py
.venv/bin/python analysis/phase3_service_times.py
.venv/bin/python analysis/phase4_synthetic_clinic.py
.venv/bin/python analysis/phase5_simulator.py
.venv/bin/python analysis/phase6_scenarios.py
```

## What each phase does

| Phase | Input | Output | Runtime |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1. Data prep | `/datasets/*` | `outputs/{kaggle,namcs,meps,cms}_*.parquet`, `data_summary.md` | ~2 min (CMS CSV is 711 MB) |
| 2. No-show model | `kaggle_clean.parquet` | `noshow_model.joblib`, `noshow_metrics.json`, 3 figures | ~30 s |
| 3. Service-time fits | `namcs_slim.parquet` | `service_times.json`, 1 figure | ~5 s |
| 4. Synthetic clinic | `cms_providers.parquet`, `meps_payer.parquet` | `clinic_providers.parquet`, `clinic_patients.parquet`, `clinic_config.json`, 1 figure | ~5 s |
| 5. Simulator | Phase 2–4 outputs | `schedule_with_p.parquet`, `baseline_smoke.parquet` | ~15 s |
| 6. Scenarios | All of the above | `scenario_results.parquet`, `scenario_summary.json`, 5 figures | ~1 min |

## Headline numbers (baseline simulation, 30 replications)

| Metric | Mean (95% CI) |
|---|---|
| Completed visits/day | 256.5 [245, 268] |
| Median wait to physician | 24.3 min [20, 37] |
| 90th-percentile wait | 40.3 min |
| Mean MD utilization | 60.3% |
| **Mean nurse utilization** | **92.9% — the binding constraint** |
| No-show rate | 19.8% |

## Policy comparison (see `figures/scenario_tradeoff.png`)

| Policy | Throughput | Median wait | MD util | Nurse util |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Baseline | 256.5 | 24.3 min | 60.3% | 92.9% |
| NAR (overbook no-show slots) | **339.4 (+32%)** | 91.3 min (+276%) | 79.4% | 123% (overloaded) |
| RBS (buffer high-risk slots) | 203.1 (-21%) | **17.6 min (-28%)** | 47.2% | 73.7% |

Policies sit on opposite ends of a throughput–vs–wait Pareto frontier. Neither resolves the nurse-stage bottleneck; staffing is the structural lever.

